message:
I read your post on [stackoverflow.com](http://stackoverflow.com) about async. This topic is hard for me to wrap my head around. I would like to ask you if there is a good example (simple project) that demonstrates this. I have a project that I am working on and I feel the thread is being blocked causing the main application to crash.

Basically, I need the "waitforinput" to be async task... at least that is what I think needs to happen.

Note: the external program I did not create and have no access to source code.

I tried thread.sleep() and other things but it did not allow the program back access to do what it needs to do. If that makes any sense.

The best example I can give inside a blog would be:

class program  
{

 static void main() //This main is executed by an external program   
 {  
 //Stuff//  
 waitforinput();  
 }  
 public void waitforinput()  
 {

 While(true); // blocks the external program from running  
 }

}
